   <note>This letter, written by James Moore King, informs his wife, Martha Batey King, that he received the clothes she sent to him. He also discusses a possible Confederate move to a front near Guyes Gap, Lee`s victory at Rapahanock, and General Kirby. King also relates that the army is in good health and asks about the return of men taken at Murfreesboro. He closes the letter with farm care instructions.</note>
